   "source": [
    "What is batch_first in collate_fn ?\n",
    "\n",
    "When dealing with sequence data (RNN/LSTM), batch_first determines the shape of the output tensor: \n",
    "\n",
    "+ batch_first=False (Default in many RNNs): Shape = (sequence_length, batch_size, feature_size)\n",
    "+ batch_first=True (More intuitive): Shape = (batch_size, sequence_length, feature_size) \n",
    "\n",
    "Using batch_first=True in collate_fn allows your data loader to directly output tensors formatted for modern models (like Transformers or LSTM with batch_first=True), avoiding a slow transpose() in the training loop."
   ]
